g.text: Anger • Lust • Divorce • Oaths • Love enemies
Inner holiness leads to true happiness\n
Practice humility, mercy, and peacemaking daily
Christians are called to influence the world\n
Be a visible witness through good works
True righteousness comes from the heart\n
Forgive, purify thoughts, love even enemies
Give to please God, not people\n
Help the poor quietly and sincerely
Relationship with God is personal and sincere\n
Pray daily in private; forgive others
Trust in God's providence over worldly worry\n
Live one day at a time, rely on God's care
Humility and self-examination before correcting others\n
Reflect on your own faults before criticizing
God answers sincere and persistent prayer\n
Approach God with trust and persistence
True discipleship = hearing and living the Word\n
Build life choices on Christ's teachings
